WEBVTT

00:00:09.280 --> 00:00:22.751 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
When eyes of blind ones see again
And ears of deaf ones hear again,

00:00:22.751 --> 00:00:35.764 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
When deserts blossom as the rose
And from parched ground fresh water flows,

00:00:35.764 --> 00:00:49.612 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
When lame ones leap just like the hart,
When loved ones never have to part,

00:00:49.612 --> 00:01:04.209 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Such blessed times you’ll realize,
If you keep your eyes on the prize.

00:01:08.088 --> 00:01:21.477 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
When tongues of mute ones speak again,
When old ones will be young again,

00:01:21.477 --> 00:01:35.074 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
When earth will yield her rich increase
And all good things will never cease,

00:01:35.074 --> 00:01:48.379 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
When songs of children fill the air,
When joy and peace are ev’rywhere,

00:01:48.379 --> 00:02:03.018 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Then, too, you’ll see the dead arise,
If you keep your eyes on the prize.

00:02:06.855 --> 00:02:20.285 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
When wolves and lambs will feed as one,
When bears and calves bask in the sun,

00:02:20.285 --> 00:02:33.340 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
A mere young boy will lead them all,
And they will heed his childish call.

00:02:33.340 --> 00:02:47.187 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
When tears belong to yesterday,
When fears and pain have passed away,

00:02:47.187 --> 00:03:07.416 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
You’ll see how God these things supplies,
If you keep your eyes on the prize.

